description._content: Image taken from: Title: "Narrative of an Expedition, undertaken under the direction of the late Mr. Assistant Surveyor E. B. Kennedy, for the exploration of the country lying between Rockingham Bay and Cape York ... To which are added, 1. The statement of the aboriginal native ... who accompanied Mr. Kennedy. 2. The statement of Dr. Vallack and Captain Dobson, who rescued the survivors ... and 3. The statement of Captain Simpson, of the “Freak,” etc. [With a map.]" Author: CARRON, William.
